# UI copy — no guide or instruction text

User-facing screens must not include setup guides, DevTools steps, env var names, or developer-only hints.

## Do not show in UI

- Environment variables (`NODE_ENV`, `AUTH_DEV_OPEN_LOGIN`, `CORS_ORIGIN`, etc.)
- CLI commands (`pnpm dev`, port numbers for debugging)
- Browser DevTools / Local Storage troubleshooting steps
- Romanized-Hindi or mixed-language dev notes (“click Login only”, “if API is production…”)
- Long paragraphs explaining how the system works internally

## Allowed

- Short labels, headings, button text (“Sign in”, “Save”)
- Brief empty/loading states (“Loading…”, “Redirecting…”)
- One-line informational footers that are product-facing (“Need access? Contact your administrator.”)
- Form field labels and placeholders

## Put documentation in README, not components

## Examples

**Bad**
```tsx
<p>Dev / non-production API: click Login only — first user is auto-created if the DB is empty.</p>
<p>If you are stuck here: browser DevTools → Application → Local Storage → delete gdms-auth.</p>
```

**Good**
```tsx
<p className="text-sm text-zinc-500">Need access? Contact your administrator.</p>
```
